<author><name><![CDATA[Stevie D]]></name></author>
<updated>2007-06-10T12:32:21+00:00</updated>
<id>https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=47&amp;p=319#p319</id>
<link href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=47&amp;p=319#p319"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Proposal to include &lt;di&gt;-like element]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=47&amp;p=319#p319"><![CDATA[
<blockquote><div><cite>Cerbera wrote:</cite><br />And what about <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;fieldset&gt;</span>s then? Shall we call those deprecated as well, since adding <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;legends&gt;</span> to a form already implies the start of a new group of form fields as well in the same manner as a <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;dt&gt;</span> does within a <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;dl&gt;</span>. Even more perhaps as only one <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;legend&gt;</span> is allowed per group which is not the case for <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;dt&gt;</span>s.<br /></div></blockquote><br /><br />There is a key difference between <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;fieldset&gt;</span> and the proposed <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;di&gt;</span>. <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;dt&gt;</span> and <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;dd&gt;</span> elements are automatically and unambiguously associated with each other. A group of one or more contiguous <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;dt&gt;</span> elements are defined by a group of one or more contiguous <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;dd&gt;</span> elements. The association is terminated by either another <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;dt&gt;</span> element or the closing <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;/dl&gt;</span> tag.<br /><br />You don't get that with elements in a <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;form&gt;</span>. Form elements may be grouped together, as in a <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;fieldset&gt;</span>, or may be stand-alone items that are not grouped with any others. So while a <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;legend&gt;</span> element will implicitly begin a <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;fieldset&gt;</span>, and in doing so terminate a previous unclosed <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;fieldset&gt;</span>, there will often be times when you need to close a <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;fieldset&gt;</span> without beginning a new one.<br /><br />Consider the following form structure:<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;form&gt;<br />Name<br />&lt;fieldset&gt;&lt;legend&gt;Address&lt;/legend&gt;<br />Address 1<br />Address 2<br />Town<br />Postcode<br />Country<br />&lt;/fieldset&gt;<br />Age<br />&lt;/form&gt;</code></dd></dl><br /><br />If you're not allowed <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;fieldset&gt;</span> elements, you can't separate off the &quot;age&quot; field at the end from the preceding &quot;address&quot; fields, other than by inserting a (completely unnecessary) <span style="font-style: italic">legend</span>.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=114">Stevie D</a> — Sun Jun 10, 2007 12:32 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
