<title type="html"><![CDATA[Proposal to include &lt;di&gt;-like element]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=47&amp;p=256#p256"><![CDATA[
(I also think form validation and <span style="font-weight: bold">&lt;dialog&gt;</span> are unnecessary additions to HTML. But I assume there's a good reason for them, just that I don't know what it is.)<br /><br />I think anyone would agree that, on the surface, <span style="font-weight: bold">&lt;di&gt;</span> is a good idea. But since the relationship is just as unambiguous without this element, it doesn't seem to add that much value. Also, we aren't talking about deprecating <span style="font-weight: bold">&lt;di&gt;</span> and replacing it with an all-new association method, we are talking about whether <span style="font-weight: bold">&lt;di&gt;</span> is worth adding.<br /><br />If you are proposing that <span style="font-weight: bold">&lt;di&gt;</span> would replace the existing grouping mechanism so that it used DOM relationships rather than element types, consider this:<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;dl&gt;<br /> &lt;di&gt;<br />  &lt;dt&gt;foo&lt;/dt&gt;<br />  &lt;dd&gt;bar&lt;/dd&gt;<br />  &lt;dt&gt;bish&lt;/dt&gt;<br />  &lt;dd&gt;bash&lt;/dd&gt;<br /> &lt;/di&gt;<br />&lt;/dl&gt;</code></dd></dl>Would this mean:<br /><ul><li>foo = bar</li><li>bish = bash</li></ul>Or:<br /><ul><li>foo, bish = bar, bash</li></ul>If it's the former, the historic association method is adequate. If it's the latter, what would happen when <span style="font-weight: bold">&lt;di&gt;</span> is absent:<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;dl&gt;<br /> &lt;dt&gt;foo&lt;/dt&gt;<br /> &lt;dd&gt;bar&lt;/dd&gt;<br /> &lt;dt&gt;bish&lt;/dt&gt;<br /> &lt;dd&gt;bash&lt;/dd&gt;<br />&lt;/dl&gt;</code></dd></dl>And what about when some but not all groups in a <span style="font-weight: bold">&lt;dl&gt;</span> are contained by a <span style="font-weight: bold">&lt;di&gt;</span>:<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;dl&gt;<br /> &lt;di&gt;<br />  &lt;dt&gt;foo&lt;/dt&gt;<br />  &lt;dd&gt;bar&lt;/dd&gt;<br /> &lt;/di&gt;<br /> &lt;dt&gt;bish&lt;/dt&gt;<br /> &lt;dd&gt;bash&lt;/dd&gt;<br /> &lt;dt&gt;alpha&lt;/dt&gt;<br /> &lt;dd&gt;beta&lt;/dt&gt;<br />&lt;/dl&gt;</code></dd></dl>I think this DOM-based method would not be backwards compatible, particularly with assistive technologies. That would make HTML5's <span style="font-weight: bold">&lt;dl&gt;</span> less accessible than HTML4's -- a very undesirable outcome.<br /><br />It's all about the nuts and bolts!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=27">Cerbera</a> — Wed May 16, 2007 8:05 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
