<title type="html"><![CDATA[Proposal to include &lt;di&gt;-like element]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=47&amp;p=255#p255"><![CDATA[
... besides, adding <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;di&gt;</span> would not just make it prettier or more readible.<br />With a <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;di&gt;</span> items within such a group would be siblings only to eachother, sharing a parent only within this group. In the current <span style="font-style: italic">&lt;dl&gt;</span> items <span style="font-weight: bold">share a parent with their cousins</span>. That doesn't really sound very semantical to me (but maybe there are some definitions of 'cousin' that I don't know about <img src="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";-)" title="Wink" />).<br /><br />Even if there are a hundred specs, laws or whatever that say this is correct or no problem, it still doesn't feel right <img src="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/images/smilies/icon_mad.gif" alt=":x" title="Mad" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=87">Sander Aarts</a> — Tue May 15, 2007 5:00 pm</p><hr />
